name: ExtensionPackagedProductDefinition_Packaging
title: Cross-version Extension `R5.PackagedProductDefinition.packaging` for use in FHIR R4
description: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element `PackagedProductDefinition.packaging` for use in FHIR R4.
purpose:
This extension is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the
element `PackagedProductDefinition.packaging` as defined in FHIR R5
in FHIR R4.

The source element is defined as:
`PackagedProductDefinition.packaging` 0..1 `BackboneElement`

Across FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as:
*  R5: `PackagedProductDefinition.packaging` 0..1 `BackboneElement`

Following are the generation technical comments:
Element `PackagedProductDefinition.packaging` is not mapped to FHIR R4, since FHIR R5 `PackagedProductDefinition` is not mapped.

element.definition: A packaging item, as a container for medically related items, possibly with other packaging items within, or a packaging component, such as bottle cap (which is not a device or a medication manufactured item).
